cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with pedestrian detection in scenes. The use of a self-learning approach and a progressive latent model suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The focus on object localization and label propagation suggests that it may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) category. Finally, the use of optimization techniques and experiments on image data suggest that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
